args: This is the last one! Let's go!
I feared the worst when so many of them\nsurrounded us, but we made it through.
You all did well. Thank you.
You're welcome—although I AM\nrather exhausted now.
Ain't there a village near here?
Yes. It is a lovely and peaceful place.
Sounds like our course is set. Let's go.
This is not what I imagined when you\ncalled this place ＂lovely and peaceful.＂
This isn't how I remember it at all...\nWhatever happened here?
Yep. Group of 'em took up residence\nnear here a little while back.
And now they keep attacking without\nwarning. We've already lost several\ngood people. ...Good friends.
Do you think she could be referring\nto the fiends that just attacked us?
You have nothing more to fear, ma'am.\nWe defeated those fiends earlier today.
It is. This village is safe now.
How can we possibly thank you?!
Did you hear that, everyone? We're saved!
Thank Ilia! Now we don't need to live\nin constant fear anymore!
My fields will be safe once more!
This calls for a celebration. Let's feast\nand make merry like never before!
Sounds like it's yer time t'shine, Su Fang!
My pyroblossoms will make a happy day\nlike this even happier!
What's with the long face, kid?\nAin't ya happy them fiends're gone?
Don't strain something patting your\nown back over this!
If you guys were so strong,\nwhy didn't you come sooner?!
If you had, Mom and Dad would...would...
Dead, yeah. Killed protecting me\nfrom those fiends.
How am I supposed to celebrate after\nsomething like that, huh?!
Ah geez, I'm sorry. This is all my fault;\nI'm the one who suggested the party.
You have done nothing wrong, sir.\nTimes like these ARE cause for celebration.
And that's exactly what we should do.\nWill everyone please set about preparing\nfor the upcoming festivities?
Maybe it's just too soon for that poor boy\nto enjoy a festival like this.
It won't be easy for him to move on. But...
But? It sounds like you have an idea.
I think I might be able to give him\nthe push he needs.
And my pyroblossoms are the key!
The day of the festival came, and Su Fang led\nthe boy somewhere in order to enact his plan...
Where are you taking me, man?\nI'm not interested in your dumb festival.
We're not going to the festival.\nWe're going...here.
I'm going to launch my pyroblossoms\nfrom here, and I wanted you to have\nthe finest seat in all the land.
I don't even know what you're talking\nabout. Can I just GO already?
You see, I also lost my parents.
Stop it! I don't need pity from—

I had just given up on my dream when I
learned the news, and that only made
me feel even more strongly that there
was nothing left to live for.
And that's why I'll never forget the\npyroblossoms I saw that night.
Their beautiful light filled me\nwith the hope to live again.
I think we should start, Su Fang.\nEveryone is waiting.
In that case, it's time to fill everyone's\nhearts with hope once more!
The flowers in the sky will mark a new\nbeginning...and bless the souls of all\nthose who we have lost.
You know, we normally don't let people\nsit this close during our displays.
But I figured I'd make an exception\nfor you just this once.
Those were...amazing.\nI've never seen anything like them.
And so as you keep on living, you can see\neven more beautiful things.
After all, hopes and dreams are things\nyou can never truly lose—you can only\nlose sight of them for a while.
